Ofgem to Review ‘Big Six’ Fuel Costs, Telegraph Says

-- B y   J o h n   S i m p s o n
-- 
2011-07-04T21:28:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-04/ofgem-to-review-big-six-fuel-costs-telegraph-says-correct-.html
(Corrects source reference in headline.)  Ofgem, the U.K. energy regulator, has
hired forensic accountants to examine the wholesale fuel prices
paid by the so-called “Big Six” energy companies after
indications of a 27 percent difference in how much suppliers
paid for electricity and 15 percent in gas last year, the  Daily
Telegraph  reported.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
John Simpson at 
 jsimpson12@bloomberg.net  